'''Maria Dudycz''' is an Australian [[health professional]] and advocate for [[people with disabilities]].<ref name=roll>[https://www.vic.gov.au/women/victorian-honour-roll-of-women/victorian-honour-roll-details-page.html?honour-roll_id=57 Dr Maria Dudycz (2018)], [[Victorian Honour Roll of Women]], [[Victorian Government]]. Accessed 12 November 2018.</ref>

Dudycz is most notable for her work developing the Victorian Disability Act 2006.<ref name=roll/><ref>Dmytryshchak, Goya (12 April 2018) [http://www.starweekly.com.au/news/womens-honour-roll-inductee-carries-torch-for-west Women's Honour Roll inductee carries torch for west], ''Star Weekly''. Retrieved 12 November 2018.</ref><ref>[https://www.odsc.vic.gov.au/about-us/legislation/#disability Legislation: Disability Act 2006], Disability Services Commissioner, Victorian Government. Accessed 12 November 2018.</ref>

Throughout her career, Dudycz's medical experience has seen her receive a number of [[Australian Government|Federal Government]] appointments.  These include chairing the Advisory Panel on the [[Breastfeeding promotion#Infant forumla marketing in hospitals|marketing]] in Australia of Infant Formula from 2001 until 2005, and directing the [[National Health and Medical Research Council]]'s Breast Cancer Centre from 2001 until 2003.<ref>[[Grant Tambling|Tambling, Grant]] (1 October 2001) [https://parlinfo.aph.gov.au/parlInfo/search/display/display.w3p;page=0;query=Source:%22PARLIAMENTARY%20SECRETARY%20-%20HEALTH%20AND%20AGED%20CARE%22;rec=1 New chair appointed to oversee special advisory panel on marketing of breast milk alternatives in Australia], Parliamentary Secretary for the Minister of Health and Aging, [[Australian Government]]. Accessed 12 November 2018.</ref>

Dudycz also chaired the Australasian College of Legal Medicine from 1998 until 2003.<ref>[https://legalmedicine.com.au/congratulations-to-dr-maria-dudycz Dr Maria Dudycz], Australian College of Legal Medicine. Accessed 12 November 2018.</ref>

In 2018, Dudycz was added to the [[Victorian Honour Roll of Women]].<ref name=roll/>

