The '''Social Responsiveness Scale''' is a quantitative measure of [[autism|autistic]] traits in 4–18 year olds.<ref name=Bolte2012>{{cite journal| pmc=3425739 | pmid=22183423 | doi=10.1007/s10803-011-1424-5 | volume=42 | title=Brief Report: the Social Responsiveness Scale for Adults (SRS-A): initial results in a German cohort | journal=J Autism Dev Disord | pages=1998–9 | last1 = Bölte | first1 = S | year=2011}}</ref><ref name=Bolte2008>{{cite journal| pmid=19360690 | doi=10.1002/aur.49 | volume=1 | title=Assessing autistic traits: cross-cultural validation of the social responsiveness scale (SRS) | year=2008 | journal=Autism Res | pages=354–63 | last1 = Bölte | first1 = S | last2 = Poustka | first2 = F | last3 = Constantino | first3 = JN}}</ref> Its [[correlation]] with behaviour problems and [[autism spectrum disorder]] symptoms has been studied.<ref name=Hus2012>{{cite journal| pmc=3504640 | pmid=22823182 | doi=10.1111/j.1469-7610.2012.02589.x | volume=54 | title=Factors influencing scores on the social responsiveness scale | journal=J Child Psychol Psychiatry | pages=216–24 | last1 = Hus | first1 = V | last2 = Bishop | first2 = S | last3 = Gotham | first3 = K | last4 = Huerta | first4 = M | last5 = Lord | first5 = C | year=2012| url=https://deepblue.lib.umich.edu/bitstream/2027.42/96433/1/j.1469-7610.2012.02589.x.pdf }}</ref><ref name=srs-ianc>[https://iancommunity.org/cs/ian_research_questions/social_responsiveness_scale_srs SRS at ianc]</ref> It can be assessed with an 18 question survey filled out by the childs parents.<ref>[https://www.vitamindcouncil.org/maternal-vitamin-d-deficiency-linked-with-autism-risk-in-children/ Maternal vitamin D deficiency linked with autism risk in children. 2016]</ref>
The list of questions is subject to copyright.<ref name=srs-ianc/>
